NAME
    tpv-ktools--get-yt-video-info

DESCRIPTION
    This script uses yt-dlp command line tool to search for track information about a YouTube video. It accepts various command-line arguments to define the search and output parameters.

SYNOPSIS
    This script retrieves detailed information about a specified track from YouTube and outputs/saves it as JSON.

EXAMPLES
    # To search for a track by artist and track title:
    ./tpv-ktools--get-yt-video-info --url "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cUjbAtHrMUc"

    # To search for a track by specifying artist and track separately:
    ./tpv-ktools--get-yt-video-info --id cUjbAtHrMUc

    # To get the Spotify URL of a track:
    ./tpv-ktools--get-yt-video-info --id B8dD0EtzVS0 --artist "The O.C. Supertones" --track "Supertones Strike Back"

PARAMETERS
    --artist, --band, --musician: The name of the artist, band, or musician.
    --track, --song, --title: The title of the track or song.
    --id, --video_id: The unique YouTube video ID
    --url, --link: full YouTube video URL
    --help, -h: Show the help text.

OUTPUT
    The script produces output as JSON from YouTube's video search using yt-dlp CLI.

    Please note that this is a third-party script and not officially supported by YouTube. Always ensure you're adhering to the terms and conditions of YouTube.
